  "title": "Electrical Panel Technician",
  "description": "<p>An Electrical Panel Technical Job involves assembling, wiring, testing, and troubleshooting industrial control panels, switchboards, and electrical systems based on schematics and technical drawings. Technicians install components like circuit breakers and PLCs, perform continuity tests, and ensure compliance with safety standards.</p><p>Key Responsibilities</p><p>Panel Assembly and Wiring: Assemble, wire, and install components (breakers, relays, PLCs) into electrical enclosures according to engineering drawings and schematics.</p><p>Testing and Commissioning: Perform point-to-point wiring continuity, functional, and safety tests to ensure panel performance before installation.</p><p>Troubleshooting and Repair: Diagnose, repair, and replace faulty electrical components, wiring, and control systems.</p><p>Maintenance and Inspection: Inspect electrical systems to detect issues and perform routine maintenance to ensure compliance with safety codes.</p><p>Documentation: Maintain accurate records of panel configurations, wiring diagrams, and test results.</p><p>Required Qualifications and Skills</p><p>Education: Technical diploma (e.g., Nitec in Electrical Engineering) or equivalent experience.</p><p>Experience: 1-3 years of experience in electrical panel assembly or maintenance.</p><p>Technical Skills: Ability to read and interpret electrical schematics, blueprints, and layout drawings.</p><p>Tools: Proficient in using hand tools, power tools, and testing equipment like multimeters.</p><p>Compliance: Knowledge of electrical codes and safety regulations (e.g., ISO, IEC).</p><p>Physical and Working Conditions</p><p>Frequently requires standing, lifting, and working in production environments.</p><p>May require on-site installation or servicing at customer locations.</p><p>Often requires following Lean manufacturing or 5S principles for workspace organization.</p><p>Time：8.00am to 5.00pm</p><p>Date：Monday to Saturday</p><p>Salary：$1,500 to $2,500</p><p>Nationality: no requirement</p>",
